cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper deals with the problem of broadcasting in wireless networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with system-state information and transmission decisions, which could place it in the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
